			  			<HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  			I truly believe that Archspace is one of the best and most solid game around as of date. Kudos to the makers.<br />
<br />
I believe most of us here have once played Archmage and / or Astronest, and IMHO, I strongly strongly believed that why Astronest flourished was because of its great gameplay, as well as it's colorful, bright and catoonish-anime like interface.<br />
<br />
I am hoping to suggest that perhaps the makers of Archspace would change the interface; not that it is not good, but i personally feel the current one now is a little dark, and most importantly, a little too wordy.<br />
<br />
Astronest used a lot of graphical icons (and colorful ones) to represent a lot of the in game features, from technology to planets, to environment and much more.<br />
<br />
I am not asking for an immediate change; just a suggestion which I hope you will take into consideration and slowly implement it in stages as the game grows, should you feel so.<br />
<br />
Anyone who feels the same? Please do not flame me, it's just that something I hope that will happen for the better (and best) of Archspace.<br />
<br />
Thanks!						<P align=right> </P>
